Ever wondered why your makeup doesn’t last all day, even with a spray? Let’s clear up the difference!

Setting Spray locks in moisture and helps your makeup blend and settle into the skin—perfect right after foundation.
Fixing Spray, on the other hand, is all about longevity. It’s used at the end to hold everything in place, like a top coat for your glam!

Pro tip: Use both for flawless, long-lasting makeup!
